        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "1e388c2226f510f8dd0f955a7b66fd140437a377",
            "subject": "LU-9119 socklnd: propagate errors on send failure"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Olaf Weber",
          "email": "olaf@sgi.com",
          "date": "2017-01-27 15:14:34.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-03 15:44:14.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: loopback NID in lnet_select_pathway()",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: loopback NID in lnet_select_pathway()\n\nIn lnet_select_pathway() sending to the loopback NID is handled\nas a special case, because there are no credits involved. (The\nloopback NID doesn't use credits, and therefore does not have\nany credits. If a message goes through the credit-managing code\nit therefore ends up waiting indefinitely for credits to become\navailable.)\n\nThe check whether we're sending over the loopback NID must be\ndone after we've completed choosing the NI to send over. In its\npresent location it only handles the case where the loopback\nNID was explicitly passed in as the source NID.\n\n(Lustre does not exercise this code path during normal operation,\nthe bug was encountered while testing code for the peer discovery\nfeature.)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: Ie7416ffd0079b8f7c6450830e55abd36c1099077\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
